'''Dreamworld Africana ''' is an [[Amusement park|Amusement]] and [[Theme Park]] situated in [[Lekki]], [[Lagos State]].

Established in 2010, Dreamworld covers an area of 10 acres (4 ha) and  re-opened to the public in 2013. The park is one of the main amusement parks in the city. The park provides many attractions to keep its visitors excited. The attractions include wet and dry facilities, bumper cars, carousal, roller coaster, trains, merry go-rounds, toddler play areas and many others.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ngrguardiannews.com/2015/11/dreamworld-africana-opens-at-christmas/|publisher=Nigerian Guardian|title=Dreamworld Africana Opens At Christmas|author=Ajibola Amzat|date=November 14, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://newtelegraphonline.com/dreamworld-africanathe-excitement-is-just-beginning/|title=DREAMWORLD AFRICANA: The excitement is just beginning|author=Andrew Iro Okungbowa|work=Travel and Tourism|publisher=New Telegraph}}{{dead link|date=September 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name =vanguard>{{cite news|publisher=the Vanguard|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2015/11/n1-5bn-dreamworld-theme-park-will-impact-nigeria-tourism/|title=N1.5bn Dreamworld theme park will impact Nigeria tourism|author=Jimoh Babatunde|accessdate=January 8, 2016|date=November 17, 2015}}</ref>

The park was initiated by private sector investors in the 2010s based on economic development funding from [[Lagos State Government]]. There are plans to expand the parks entertainment facilities and attractions.<ref name =vanguard/>

