'''Margo''' is the screen and stage name of Margo Timon (née Tucker), a [[Magic (illusion)|magic]] performer and actress who had a starring slot in the [[NBC]] network television special ''[[The World's Most Dangerous Magic]] II''. She worked with the duo [[The Pendragons]].<ref name="imdb">{{IMDb name|id=2438275|name=Margo}}</ref>

==Life and career==
Margo is the offspring of an old established magic family. Her mother is award-winning magician [[Frances Willard (magician)|Frances Willard]]. Margo's father is Texan newspaper editor Glenn Tucker. Her younger sister Hannah is married to close-up magic specialist and lecturer [[Michael Ammar]].{{citation needed|date=September 2015}}

As an assistant with The Pendragons, Margo appeared on ''[[The Tonight Show]]'' and the ''World Magic Awards''. In 1999 she was picked by producer [[Gary Ouellet]] to be one of the stars of the second of his ''World's Most Dangerous Magic'' specials. Ouellet and his team created for her the [[predicament escape]] trick "Rat Attack", in which she was shackled into a coffin-like box which was then filled with rats and she then magically escaped.<ref name="imdb"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.camirandmagic.com/en_gary_inmemo.html|title=''In memory of Gary Q Ouellet''|publisher=Camirand Academy of Magic, Inc.|accessdate=2007-03-08}}</ref> She studied acting and had small roles in the television series ''[[Night Court]]'' and ''[[The Young and the Restless]]''.<ref name="imdb"/>

==Marriage==
In 1996, she married James Timon who was head of entertainment at [[Universal Studios Hollywood|Universal Studios]]. The couple first met because Timon had hired The Pendragons for a run at Universal and Margo was working with them.<ref name="imdb"/>

